      • onClose

        public void onClose(Status status,
                    Metadata.Trailers trailers)
        Description copied from class: Call.Listener
        The Call has been closed. No further sending or receiving can occur. If status is not equal to Status.OK, then the call failed. An additional block of trailer metadata may be received at the end of the call from the server. An empty Metadata object is passed if no trailers are received.
        Specified by:
        onClose in class Call.Listener<T>
        Parameters:
        status - the result of the remote call.
        trailers - metadata provided at call completion.

      • onReady

        public void onReady(int numMessages)
        Description copied from class: Call.Listener
        This indicates that the Call is now capable of sending the given number of messages (via Call.sendPayload(RequestT)) without requiring excessive buffering internally. This event is just a suggestion and the application is free to ignore it, however doing so may result in excessive buffering within the Call.

        NOTE: this method is not yet implemented!

        Overrides:
        onReady in class Call.Listener<T>
        Parameters:
        numMessages - the number of messages that can be sent without requiring excessive buffering.
